This paper proposes a deep learning-based method for colored transparent object matting from a single image. The problem involves computer vision (CV) and graphics (GR) as it requires estimating an object mask and a refractive flow field. The proposed method uses a deep learning framework, which falls under artificial intelligence (AI) and machine learning (LG) categories. Additionally, the paper involves creating a large-scale synthetic dataset, which can be considered as multimedia (MM) research. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.AI, cs.LG, and cs.MM.
